whether money has involved or not, so you now require that money be a factor in the exchange and also require a public auction site to be involved for you to be aware of the fact to be bothered.<br><br>Too many specific factors involved at this point, I have to believe money alone can't take an acceptable violation of the EULA into &quot;De-guild him or I'm gone~!&quot;<br><br>If your concern doesn't revolve entirely around money you need to understand a few things.<br><br>Bako/Caparelli played Dante a Cleric on the first Plane of Hate raid on the server.  The reason for this was fun, the 4th (I think, been awhile) Cleric on the raid would provide more benefit than a low 50's munk.<br><br>This violated the EULA as much as Eldraed III playing does.  The EULA doesn't allowing for borrowing characters anymore than it does buying.<br><br>The original Caparelli left the server long ago, has since returned.  Because Fire and Fury could do more things, and have more fun, with an Enchanter at raids Bako took over the account.<br><br>This violates the EULA.<br><br>Fire and Fury wiped out on Zlandicar and HUmle was logged on by another guild member to summon the corpses rather than hauling out non-stackable coffins or leaving the corpses there until HUmle himself logged on.<br><br>This violates the EULA.<br><br>I had trouble believing how much a rogue could out-damage me in Sleeper's Tomb combined with other factors led to me playing a Rogue in that zone, I had fun, although was deeply embarassed for my main, playing a melee for the first time in about 6 months and by far the best equipped melee I had ever played.<br><br>This violates the EULA.<br><br>500 dollars, the amount listed for selling the fully equipped Eldraed on player auctions, is a good take home wage for a full weeks work.  It's a good 2 week paycheck for a student working at McDonalds.<br><br>In less than a week I could easily level an Ogre SK by buying Eldraed's gear to lvl 38 and then group in Velk's Lab with people far above my level to continue to level quickly to 55.  Seeing as Eldraed is not used in a tanking role in AS at this point he would have the majority of original Eldraed's DPS and if AS was looking for an SK could likely join the guild.<br><br>Would this be earning the right to play in the high end game or would this be worth an ultimatum to de-guild?<br><br>I could buy Nabiki and PL an SK to 55 in 2 weeks and then apply to AS.<br><br>Would this be earning the right to play in the high end game or would this be worth an ultimatum to de-guild?<br><br>I could make a lvl 1 SK on FV and transfer him to Legends and twink him out with gear from past characters and PL him and further equip him on Stormhammer and return to FV as a Gravelord (the one month minimum Legends duration breaks a pattern somewhat).  And then apply to AS.<br><br>Would this be earning the right to play in the high end game or would this be worth an ultimatum to de-guild?<br><br>These 3 examples closely parralel Fire and Fury members, one of them former.  I was guilded with all of them and had concerns about none of them because I have fun killing mobs and looting them, not worrying about how my guildmates got to 60 let alone worrying about how people in other guilds got to 60.<br><br>When it comes down to money, I won't buy or sell.  My primary concern with selling is it demoralizes people to equipping vital classes because it paints stormclouds on the horizon, my concern with buying is that someone who needs the shortcut to 60 quite possibly can't/won't play enough to be an effective raider at 60.<br><br>The EULA doesn't concern me, it largely exists to protect Verant.  If Verant acknowledged that a Scepter of Destruction was worth $$ that would mean that if a loss of code meant your toon lost that item you would be able to sue Verant for the loss.<br><br>Verant has always deliberately turned a blind eye to account sharing and selling except in the most extreme and public situations, because their concern is foremost that as many people as possible have fun playing the game resulting in them making money and secondly to protect themselves from being sued to keep that money.<br><br>If you're not having fun because your guildmates don't follow the EULA then feel free to proclaim it's them or me, someone is out of the guild.  <br><br>If you're not having fun because someone you won't/never/rarely grouped/raided/chatted with/met is now played by a different RL person that's your own problem.<br><br>If you want to come to FV Soapbox and bring up something that bothers you feel free, it's what the forum was used for, might even still be used for post &quot;pruning&quot;.  But if you do please bring a little more to the table, if it wasn't for Capt Roleplay agreeing with Heagan making it a landmark thread I felt compelled to post on, it's just another narrow example pointed at those people you love to hate.<br><br>The number of people in my experience who will de-guild over account sharing is very limited, Heagan stating that it was a contributing factor in his decision to de-guild is the first time I've seen such severity attached to the issue from someone playing in the high end game.  Zsuzsana may agree with the sentiment of uphold the EULA, I would be absolutely shocked if she de-guilded over it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umadrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>madrain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kerran Lord</span><br>  Posts: 707<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/20/02 6:43:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1248.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Where's the Beef?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 500 doll